---
title: Seared Beef Rump & Ginger-Peanut Sauce with Roast Veggies & Crisp Pear Slaw
description: Get a little crazy with beef steak and veggies but adding a nutty soy sauce over the beef. The pop of ginger will get your tastebuds excited for the next bite. If you need a moment of peace, the fresh pear slaw is sure to balance the dish out. You’ll never want your steak and veggies any other way!

*This recipe is under 650kcal per serving and under 40g carbohydrates per serving.*

